note.body:
get_object_path_header() inside g_dbus_message_get_path() can return NULL.
Also g_strdup() can return NULL whose return value is passed to strrchr()
```
  path = g_dbus_message_get_path (message);
  subtree_path = g_strdup (path);
  needle = strrchr (subtree_path, '/');
```

And then below assert check is also redundant?
```
  object_path = g_dbus_message_get_path (message);
  g_assert (object_path != NULL);
```

